## Query (H) — Customers who spent more than the average customer (high-spenders)

```sql
SELECT c.first_name || ' ' || c.last_name AS customer,
       ROUND(SUM(oi.quantity * oi.unit_price * (1 - oi.discount_applied)), 2) AS total_spent
FROM CUSTOMER c
JOIN ORDERS o ON c.customer_id = o.customer_id
JOIN ORDER_ITEM oi ON o.order_id = oi.order_id
GROUP BY c.customer_id
HAVING total_spent > (
    SELECT AVG(sub.total) FROM (
        SELECT SUM(oi2.quantity * oi2.unit_price * (1 - oi2.discount_applied)) AS total
        FROM ORDERS o2
        JOIN ORDER_ITEM oi2 ON o2.order_id = oi2.order_id
        GROUP BY o2.customer_id
    ) sub
)
ORDER BY total_spent DESC;
```

| customer   | total_spent |
| ---------- | ----------- |
| Bob Nguyen | 1576.54     |

*1 row(s) returned.*

